  This document describes the usage of runmake, the Trilinos make utility.
  
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
I.  Prerequisites

  In order for the make utility to work, you must have the following in place:
  
    1. You must have a correctly configured build directory.
       
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
II.  Execution

  To execute the Trilinos make utility, simply type:
  
    cd /PATH/TO/Trilinos/commonTools/test/utilities/
    runmake --help
            
  for information on required and optional arguments.
  
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
IV.  Make Results File

  The results of the make attempt will be placed in the specified output
  directory and will be named according to the following scheme:
  
    make_YR-MO-DA_HR.MN.SE.txt
  
  The test results files will consist of the following:
  
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------------+
  |HOST_NAME        = herouxsmp
  |DNS_NAME         = cs.csbsju.edu
  |HOST_OS          = linux
  |
  |TRILINOS_DIR     = /u/TrilinosTestHarness/TrilinosRelease5.0/Trilinos/
  |BRANCH           = trilinos-release-5-0-branch
  |
  |BUILD_DIR        = SERIAL2/
  |COMM             = serial
  |
  |START_TIME       = 2005-03-31 16:40:23
  |END_TIME         = 2005-03-31 16:40:25
  |RUN_TIME         = 00:00:02
  |
  |EXIT_STATUS      = 0
  |RESULT           = pass
  |
  |BROKEN_PACKAGE   = NONE
  |
  |BEGIN_MAKE_OUTPUT
  |
  |  Hello, World.
  |  *** test passed ***
  |
  |END_MAKE_OUTPUT
  |
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------------+

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------